As far as helping people camp Emp Key parts ROFL... I believe we called it SSRA week....  I was their every day for atleast 3-4 hours a day when everyday only 20-25 MiM (wearing flags) would log on... It was hell..  BTW I had my key a longggg time before that..  Whatever tho I believe everyone in their right mind will agree that week sucked but what do you know MiM got what 50+ Emp keys in that one week... Thanks.. <br>
<br>
Ssra Shards well I will fess up to not camping Ssra Shards like I did Emp Keys but I decided to put my time into some personal fun instead of the guild on this one for a few reasons besides being burnt out from Ssra week.  <br>
<br>
1.  I knew when we first killed Emperor we had about 30+ who were about ready for VT.<br>
<br>
2.  I knew after we killed our first Emperor a TON of people would be working on their shards (which happend).<br>
<br>
3.  After 2nd Emperor kill I knew VT would be coming soon.  Thus people rush more to get shards(which happend)..<br>
<br>
So your probably asking yourself WTF does that mean? I tell you what it means... It means personal motivation... do what it takes to get it done...  The GUILD (or majority of it) wanted to get into VT, which really wasn't the case for Emperor IMO we had to basically &quot;force&quot; the guild to get their emp keys done..  Some people busted their asses some people got lucky Shards weren't fun (I think I was one of the lucky ones..)  The way I got my shards was I asked in /guild if anyone wanted to go camp some...  Got a group and went and camped a particular shard until everyone in that group got one thanks...  <br>
<br>
<br>
People that say I never did anything for MiM really make me sad... Just because I make a personal choice to move on, they try to make me look like someone or something that I am not..<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Some people make think its bad but this is the way I feel on leaving MiM and applying to AD on the same day..  Do I get paid to play EQ? ummm no..  So I straight up told MiM in my deguilding post on their guild message board my intentions to apply to AD and carried them out...  Did what I wanted to do and sticking by that..  <br>
