<br>
In terms of game play, she's a great player, one of the best shamen I've played with.  In raids, I would always ask for buffs and would get it fast (I think only Zodon is the only person faster) and buff me after I died before I asked, so I doubt she was as afk as alot of people are saying.  In terms of raiding, she's fairly active, certainly not the most active in guild, but is always there when she's on.  <br>
<br>
I consider Cilla a friend(still), as she has always been helpful, whenever I asked.  <br>
<br>
Now, despite this, I still think her excuse for leaving the guild was alot of BS.  She has given me three reasons: first that the leadership was weak, second she was worried that Kat would leave and our raids would stop, and third, that she wanted to see higher level content before EQ eventually ended.<br>
<br>
The first reason I think is BS (I've told her this) because the leadership has always been the same when she joined this guild and throughtout the last 9 months.  And the leadership actually affects our play very little.<br>
<br>
The second reason is also BS because I told her that we're expanding the raid leadership to include 4 others, so that responsibility was more spread (just in case Kat leaves) and for her to wait it out a month or two to see how well we do with this new system, but she couldn't wait and bolted 2 days later.<br>
<br>
I think the third reason hits the marks.  She wants to see higher level content (and loot). Despite the fact that the guild helped her obtain all those equipment she has now, she rather go to another guild than help build this one go there, and that pissed off alot of people.<br>
<br>
So my summary of Cilla: <br>
Strentgh: Great shaman, helpful in guild<br>
